QA / QC Engineer
-
Date Posted: 2014/05/02 14:00:32
Ref. JB3046615
Job Description
Progressive Engineering and Construction Division is currently representing an established regional MEP Contractor with operations across the GCC and Middle East. With over 5,000 employees and numerous multi billion dollar projects underway, our client is looking to expand its team on a new mixed use development. Recently, our Client was awarded a 1 Billion AED MEP contract in Kazakhstan to work on a multi billion dollar development in anticipation of the 2017 Kazakhstan Expo. Due to the size of the project, QA/QC Engineers are needed to join the operations in Astana, Kazakhstan. The position will be a permanent hire but will have a frequent rotation. A successful QA/QC Engineer will meet the below requirements: Degree qualified 10 Years Post Graduate Experience MEP experience on Hotels, Towers, Malls and Hospitals Must have worked with MEP Contractors If interested, please reply with your WORD CV or if you have any questions please contact Rishita Jain at +91 (0)22 61623518.
Skills
Progressive Engineering and Construction Division is currently representing an established regional MEP Contractor with operations across the GCC and Middle East. With over 5,000 employees and numerous multi billion dollar projects underway, our client is looking to expand its team on a new mixed use development.
Recently, our Client was awarded a 1 Billion AED MEP contract in Kazakhstan to work on a multi billion dollar development in anticipation of the 2017 Kazakhstan Expo. Due to the size of the project, QA/QC Engineers are needed to join the operations in Astana, Kazakhstan.
The position will be a permanent hire but will have a frequent rotation.
A successful QA/QC Engineer will meet the below requirements:
Degree qualified
10 Years Post Graduate Experience
MEP experience on Hotels, Towers, Malls and Hospitals
Must have worked with MEP Contractors
If interested, please reply with your WORD CV or if you have any questions please contact Rishita Jain at +91 (0)22 61623518
